  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The objective of this trial is to evaluate the clinical effectiveness of the administration
      of a depigmented and polymerized allergen extract of Olea europaea in the rhinitis or
      allergic rhinoconjunctivitis
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Immunotherapy is a specific treatment for allergic diseases. Unlike conventional
      pharmacological treatment, immunotherapy is the only treatment that could modify the natural
      course of allergic disease. This is a prospective double-blind placebo controlled study with
      two arms of treatment: placebo and active.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
